				\begin{document}$$ \Delta \sigma = {\upxi} \times \left( {\mu _{\mathrm{e}} + \mu _{\mathrm{h}}} \right) = - \frac{{{\mathrm{\Delta }}E_{{\mathrm{exc}}}(\omega )}}{{{\mathrm{\Delta }}E_{{\mathrm{gx}}}(\omega )}}\frac{{c\varepsilon _0}}{{{\mathrm{Fe}}_0}}\frac{1}{{1 - e^{ - \alpha L}}}, $$\end{document}where ξ is quantum yield of charge generation, μe and μh are the electron and hole mobility, respectively, ΔEexc is the THz electric field transmitted through the sample after photo excitation while ΔEgs is the ground state THz electric field, ε0 is permittivity of vacuum, c is velocity of light, F is the fluence in ph cm−2, e0 is the elementary charge, α is the absorption coefficient, and L the thickness of the sample. The quantity that is obtained from the above equation has the unit of mobility in cm2 V−1 s−1.
